BT 1 0 0 1 0 48.3 Tm .308618 Tw 14.5 TL /F1 9.7 Tf .109804 .141176 .2 rg (Electrons are far too small and fast for Newtonian mechanics to describe accurately. Instead, their behaviour) Tj T* 0 Tw .357229 Tw (is captured by a ) Tj /F2 9.7 Tf (wavefunction) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf ( - a mathematical expression whose square gives the probability of finding an) Tj T* 0 Tw .659748 Tw (electron at a particular point in space. Solving for these wavefunctions is what generates the familiar shells,) Tj T* 0 Tw (subshells and orbitals of chemistry.) Tj T* ET
