BT 1 0 0 1 13 33.8 Tm 14.5 TL /F2 9.7 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (\273) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf .109804 .141176 .2 rg (  ) Tj /F2 9.7 Tf (Non-relativistic systems) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf ( are handled by the ) Tj /F2 9.7 Tf (Schrodinger equation) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf (, written compactly as ) Tj /F4 9.7 Tf (H) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf /F5 9.7 Tf 14.5 TL (y) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf 14.5 TL ( = E) Tj /F5 9.7 Tf 14.5 TL (y) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf 14.5 TL (,) Tj T* (where ) Tj /F4 9.7 Tf (H) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf ( is the Hamiltonian \(total-energy\) operator, ) Tj /F5 9.7 Tf 14.5 TL (y) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf 14.5 TL ( is the wavefunction and E is the allowed energy \(an) Tj T* (eigenvalue\). It works well for lighter atoms.) Tj T* ET
