BT 1 0 0 1 0 48.3 Tm .047554 Tw 14.5 TL /F1 9.7 Tf .109804 .141176 .2 rg (Each electron in an atom is uniquely described by a set of four ) Tj /F2 9.7 Tf (quantum numbers) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf (. Together they specify the) Tj T* 0 Tw .738004 Tw (size, shape, spatial orientation and spin of the orbital the electron occupies. The ) Tj /F2 9.7 Tf (Pauli exclusion principle) Tj /F1 9.7 Tf  T* 0 Tw .297579 Tw (guarantees that no two electrons in the same atom share an identical set of all four - which is why orbitals fill) Tj T* 0 Tw (in the orderly way they do.) Tj T* ET
