BT 1 0 0 1 0 65.7 Tm .12759 Tw 15.2 TL /F5 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (Quality Assurance \(QA\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf ( is the wide umbrella. A ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (quality-assurance system \(QAS\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( is the creation and operation of) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.794003 Tw (the standards, procedures and management systems that together guarantee the quality of a drug. It is how) Tj T* 0 Tw .804223 Tw (management gives the customer and the wider community a dependable promise of quality, monitoring the whole) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.00734 Tw (journey from acquisition of a pharmaceutical raw material to conversion into a finished product placed in the) Tj T* 0 Tw (patient\222s hands. QA is best summarised by the relationship ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .541176 .415686 .058824 rg (QA = QC + GMP) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 57.02362 177.9583 cm
q
BT 1 0 0 1 0 50.5 Tm 15.2 TL /F5 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (Quality Control \(QC\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf ( is a subset of QA focused on testing and verification \227 confirming that a product meets) Tj T* (predefined specifications. It uses analytical techniques \(HPLC, spectroscopy and the like\) on raw materials,) Tj T* -0.03206 Tw (in-process samples and finished products to confirm potency, purity and stability, and to identify and reject defective) Tj T* 0 Tw (batches. QC is essentially ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (reactive) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (: it detects problems after production has occurred.) Tj T* ET
