BT 1 0 0 1 0 65.7 Tm 3.240696 Tw 15.2 TL /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (When light passes through a coloured solution, certain wavelengths are selectively absorbed, producing an) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.783838 Tw (absorption spectrum; the light that is not absorbed is transmitted and gives the solution its colour. Two linked) Tj T* 0 Tw .307197 Tw (quantities describe this: ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (transmittance \(T\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (, the fraction of light passing through, and ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (absorbance \(A\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (, related by ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .541176 .415686 .058824 rg (A) Tj T* 0 Tw .012359 Tw (= log\(1/T\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (. The ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (Beer\226Lambert law) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( \227 that absorbance is proportional to concentration and path length \227 underlies) Tj T* 0 Tw (quantification across photometry, colorimetry and spectrophotometry.) Tj T* ET
