BT 1 0 0 1 0 80.9 Tm 1.357676 Tw 15.2 TL /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (Immunoassays exploit an antibody\222s ability to recognise and bind one specific macromolecule out of a complex) Tj T* 0 Tw .955153 Tw (mixture. The bound macromolecule is the ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (antigen) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (; the precise region on it that the antibody grips is the ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (epitope) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (,) Tj T* 0 Tw .966397 Tw (while the antibody\222s binding site is its ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (paratope) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (. Binding is driven by non-covalent forces \227 hydrogen bonding,) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.07214 Tw (electrostatic, van der Waals and hydrophobic interactions \227 giving a very high affinity constant \(Ka ) Tj /F6 10.3 Tf 15.2 TL (\273) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf 15.2 TL ( 10) Tj /F4 8.3 Tf 5.15 Ts (7) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf 0 Ts (\22610) Tj /F4 8.3 Tf 5.15 Ts (12) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf 0 Ts  T* 0 Tw .636539 Tw (L/mol\) that lets the assay detect trace analytes in blood, plasma or urine. The four prerequisites are an ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (antigen) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (, an) Tj T* 0 Tw /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (antibody) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (, the ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (analyte) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( and a ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (label) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (.) Tj T* ET
