BT 1 0 0 1 0 80.9 Tm .612643 Tw 15.2 TL /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (In a ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (competitive \(inhibition\) immunoassay) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (, unlabelled analyte from the sample competes with a fixed amount of) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.265203 Tw /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (labelled analyte \(tracer, Ag*\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( for a limited number of antibody sites. The signal is ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (inversely) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( related to analyte) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.289559 Tw (concentration: more analyte ) Tj /F6 10.3 Tf 15.2 TL (\256) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf 15.2 TL ( less tracer bound ) Tj /F6 10.3 Tf 15.2 TL (\256) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf 15.2 TL ( lower signal. This format suits small molecules \(haptens \227) Tj T* 0 Tw .04928 Tw (drugs, hormones, pesticides, mycotoxins\) that carry only one epitope. In a ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (non-competitive \(immunometric\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( assay,) Tj T* 0 Tw .271556 Tw (antibody is present in excess and the signal is ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (directly) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( proportional to analyte; these give superior sensitivity, wider) Tj T* 0 Tw (range and greater specificity, and suit larger multi-epitope analytes \(proteins, peptides\).) Tj T* ET
