BT 1 0 0 1 0 65.7 Tm .937436 Tw 15.2 TL /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (A microbiological assay compares the inhibition of microbial growth produced by an antibiotic under test against) Tj T* 0 Tw .48809 Tw (that produced by known concentrations of a standard preparation of the same antibiotic. Two standard methods are) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.14687 Tw (used: the ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (cylinder-plate \(cup-plate\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( method, which measures zones of inhibition around wells of antibiotic on a) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.557653 Tw (seeded plate, and the ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (turbidimetric \(tube\)) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( method, which measures growth suppression as reduced turbidity in) Tj T* 0 Tw (liquid culture.) Tj T* ET
