BT 1 0 0 1 0 80.9 Tm .609638 Tw 15.2 TL /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (A ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (bioassay) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( is the comparative assessment of the relative potency of a test compound against a standard, measured) Tj T* 0 Tw .47392 Tw (on living or biological tissue. It quantifies the amount of active principle in a pharmaceutical or biological material) Tj T* 0 Tw .421063 Tw (using a suitable biological system. Bioassays come in three types: ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (direct assays) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (; ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (indirect graded assays) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( \(response) Tj T* 0 Tw .095403 Tw (rises with dose, potency read from a standard response curve \227 e.g. acetylcholine contracting frog rectus abdominis) Tj T* 0 Tw 3.509037 Tw (muscle\); and ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf .709804 .070588 0 rg (indirect quantal \("all-or-none"\) assays) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg ( \(e.g. digitalis-induced cardiac arrest in guinea pigs,) Tj T* 0 Tw (insulin-induced hypoglycaemic convulsions in mice, LD) Tj /F4 8.3 Tf -5.15 Ts (50) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf 0 Ts (/ED) Tj /F4 8.3 Tf -5.15 Ts (50) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf 0 Ts ( comparisons\).) Tj T* ET
