BT 1 0 0 1 0 65.7 Tm .69022 Tw 15.2 TL /F5 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (When is a bioassay indicated?) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf ( When a chemical method is unavailable, too complex, or insensitive to low doses) Tj T* 0 Tw .146553 Tw (\(e.g. histamine\); when the active principle is unknown or cannot be isolated/purified \(e.g. insulin, posterior-pituitary) Tj T* 0 Tw 3.481546 Tw (extract, peptide hormones\); to compare potency of a drug from different sources \(e.g. cardiac glycosides,) Tj T* 0 Tw .095234 Tw (catecholamines\); and where biological activity cannot be captured chemically \(e.g. cis- vs trans-methylphenidate\). It) Tj T* 0 Tw (also underpins biological standardisation of natural products such as oxytocin, vasopressin, insulin and heparin.) Tj T* ET
