BT 1 0 0 1 0 96.1 Tm 1.29206 Tw 15.2 TL /F5 10.3 Tf .109804 .141176 .203922 rg (Principles.) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf ( Compare the test substance with the International Standard preparation of the same agent; determine) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.536032 Tw (how much test substance produces the same biological effect as the standard; ensure the activity assayed is the) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.18334 Tw (activity of interest; use standard and test with similar pharmacological effects and mode of action; and minimise) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.147556 Tw (biological variation \(constant conditions; animals of the same species, sex and weight; enough animals to reduce) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.995239 Tw (individual-variation error\). ) Tj /F5 10.3 Tf (Accuracy limits:) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf ( within \26120% of true value is good, within \26110% is excellent.) Tj T* 0 Tw 6.042185 Tw /F5 10.3 Tf (Drawbacks:) Tj /F4 10.3 Tf ( biological variation, troublesome and time-consuming, expensive, and less accurate than) Tj T* 0 Tw (physicochemical methods.) Tj T* ET
